 0419:     """
 0420:     Susceptible, Infected, Removed (SIR)
 0421:     
 0422:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 0423:     * Is: symptomatic 
 0424: 
 0425:     ...
 0426: 
 0427:     Parameters
 0428:     ----------
 0429:     parameters: dict
 0430:         Contains the following keys:
 0431: 
 0432:         alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 0433:             Fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 0434:         beta: float, np.array (M,)
 0435:             Rate of spread of infection.
 0436:         gIa: float, np.array (M,)
 0437:             Rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 0438:         gIs: float, np.array (M,)
 0439:             Rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 0440:         fsa: float, np.array (M,)
 0441:             Fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 0442:     M: int
 0443:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 0444:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 0445:     Ni: np.array(M, )
 0446:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 0447:     
 0448:     Examples
 0449:     --------
 0450:     An example of the SIR class  
 0451: 
 0452:     >>> M = 1                   # SIR model with no age structure
 0453:     >>> Ni = 1000*np.ones(M)    # only one age group
 0454:     >>> N = np.sum(Ni)          # total population 
 0455:     >>> 
 0456:     >>> beta  = 0.2             # Infection rate
 0457:     >>> gIa   = 0.1             # Removal rate of asymptomatic infectives
 0458:     >>> gIs   = 0.1             # Removal rate of symptomatic infectives
 0459:     >>> alpha = 0               # Fraction of asymptomatic infectives
 0460:     >>> fsa   = 1               # self-isolation of symtomatic infectives
 0461:     >>> 
 0462:     >>> Ia0 = np.array([0])     # Intial asymptomatic infectives
 0463:     >>> Is0 = np.array([1])     # Initial symptomatic
 0464:     >>> R0  = np.array([0])     # No removed individuals initially
 0465:     >>> S0  = N-(Ia0+Is0+R0)    # S + Ia + Is + R = N
 0466:     >>> 
 0467:     >>> # there is no contact structure
 0468:     >>> def contactMatrix(t):
 0469:     >>>     return np.identity(M)
 0470:     >>> 
 0471:     >>> # duration of simulation and data file
 0472:     >>> Tf = 160;  Nt=160;
 0473:     >>> 
 0474:     >>> # instantiate model
 0475:     >>> parameters = {'alpha':alpha, 'beta':beta, 'gIa':gIa, 'gIs':gIs,'fsa':fsa}
 0476:     >>> model = pyross.deterministic.SIR(parameters, M, Ni)
 0477:     >>> 
 0478:     >>> # simulate model using two possible ways
 0479:     >>> data1 = model.simulate(S0, Ia0, Is0, contactMatrix, Tf, Nt)                    
 0480:     >>> data2 = model.simulator(np.concatenate((S0, Ia0, Is0)), contactMatrix, Tf, Nt) 
 0481:     """
 0482: 
 0483: 
+0484:     def __init__(self, parameters, M, Ni):

 1176:     """
 1177:     Susceptible, Exposed, Infected, Removed (SEI8R)
 1178:     The infected class has 8 groups:
 1179: 
 1180:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1181:     * Is: symptomatic
 1182:     * Ih: hospitalized
 1183:     * Ic: ICU
 1184:     * Im: Mortality
 1185: 
 1186:     Is ---> Ih, Is'-> R
 1187:     Ih ---> Ic, Ih'-> R
 1188:     Ic ---> Im, Ic'-> R
 1189: 
 1190:     ...
 1191: 
 1192:     Parameters
 1193:     ----------
 1194:     parameters: dict
 1195:         Contains the following keys:
 1196: 
 1197:         alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 1198:             Fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1199:         beta: float
 1200:             Rate of spread of infection.
 1201:         gE: float
 1202:             Rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 1203:         gIa: float
 1204:             Rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1205:         gIs: float
 1206:             Rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1207:         gIsp: float
 1208:             Rate of removal from symptomatic individuals towards buffer.
 1209:         gIh: float
 1210:             Rate of removal for hospitalised individuals.
 1211:         gIhp: float
 1212:             Rate of removal from hospitalised individuals towards buffer.
 1213:         gIc: float
 1214:             Rate of removal for idividuals in intensive care.
 1215:         gIcp: float
 1216:             Rate of removal from ICU individuals towards buffer.
 1217:         fsa: float
 1218:             Fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1219:         fh  : float
 1220:             Fraction by which hospitalised individuals are isolated.
 1221:         sa: float, np.array (M,)
 1222:             Daily arrival of new susceptables.
 1223:         hh: float, np.array (M,)
 1224:             Fraction hospitalised from Is
 1225:         cc: float, np.array (M,)
 1226:             Fraction sent to intensive care from hospitalised.
 1227:         mm: float, np.array (M,)
 1228:             mortality rate in intensive care
 1229:     M: int
 1230:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1231:         I.e len(contactMatrix)

 1586:     """
 1587:     Susceptible, Exposed, Activated, Infected, Removed (SEAI5R)
 1588:     The infected class has 8 groups:
 1589: 
 1590:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1591:     * Is: symptomatic
 1592:     * Ih: hospitalized
 1593:     * Ic: ICU
 1594:     * Im: Mortality
 1595: 
 1596:     Is ---> Ih, Is'-> R
 1597:     Ih ---> Ic, Ih'-> R
 1598:     Ic ---> Im, Ic'-> R
 1599: 
 1600:     ...
 1601: 
 1602:     Parameters
 1603:     ----------
 1604:     parameters: dict
 1605:         Contains the following keys:
 1606: 
 1607:         alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 1608:             Fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1609:         beta: float
 1610:             Rate of spread of infection.
 1611:         gE: float
 1612:             Rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 1613:         gIa: float
 1614:             Rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1615:         gIs: float
 1616:             Rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1617:         gIsp: float
 1618:             Rate of removal from symptomatic individuals towards buffer.
 1619:         gIh: float
 1620:             Rate of removal for hospitalised individuals.
 1621:         gIhp: float
 1622:             Rate of removal from hospitalised individuals towards buffer.
 1623:         gIc: float
 1624:             Rate of removal for idividuals in intensive care.
 1625:         gIcp: float
 1626:             Rate of removal from ICU individuals towards buffer.
 1627:         fsa: float
 1628:             Fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1629:         fh  : float
 1630:             Fraction by which hospitalised individuals are isolated.
 1631:         sa: float, np.array (M,)
 1632:             Daily arrival of new susceptables.
 1633:         hh: float, np.array (M,)
 1634:             Fraction hospitalised from Is
 1635:         cc: float, np.array (M,)
 1636:             Fraction sent to intensive care from hospitalised.
 1637:         mm: float, np.array (M,)
 1638:             mortality rate in intensive care
 1639:     M: int
 1640:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1641:         I.e len(contactMatrix)

 1842:     Susceptible, Exposed, Asymptomatic and infected, 
 1843:     Infected, Removed, Quarantined (SEAIRQ)
 1844: 
 1845:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1846:     * Is: symptomatic
 1847:     * E: exposed
 1848:     * A: asymptomatic and infectious
 1849:     * Q: quarantined 
 1850: 
 1851:     ...
 1852: 
 1853:     Parameters
 1854:     ----------
 1855:     parameters: dict
 1856:         Contains the following keys:
 1857: 
 1858:         alpha: float
 1859:             Fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1860:         beta: float, np.array (M,)
 1861:             Rate of spread of infection.
 1862:         gIa: float, np.array (M,)
 1863:             Rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1864:         gIs: float, np.array (M,)
 1865:             Rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1866:         gE: float, np.array (M,)
 1867:             Rate of removal from exposed individuals.
 1868:         gA: float, np.array (M,)
 1869:             Rate of removal from activated individuals.
 1870:         fsa: float, np.array (M,)
 1871:             Fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1872:         tE: float, np.array (M,)
 1873:             testing rate and contact tracing of exposeds
 1874:         tA: float, np.array (M,)
 1875:             testing rate and contact tracing of activateds
 1876:         tIa: float, np.array (M,)
 1877:             testing rate and contact tracing of asymptomatics
 1878:         tIs: float, np.array (M,)
 1879:             testing rate and contact tracing of symptomatics
 1880:     M: int
 1881:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1882:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 1883:     Ni: np.array(M, )

static char __pyx_doc_4core_13deterministic_14SEAIRQ_testing_4simulate[] = "\n        Simulates a compartment model given initial conditions,\n        choice of integrator and other parameters. \n        Returns the time series data and parameters in a dict. \n        Internaly calls the method 'simulator' of CommonMethods\n        \n        ...\n\n        Parameters\n        ----------\n        S0: np.array\n            Initial number of susceptables.\n        E0: np.array\n            Initial number of exposeds.\n        A0: np.array\n            Initial number of activateds.\n        Ia0: np.array\n            Initial number of asymptomatic infectives.\n        Is0: np.array\n            Initial number of symptomatic infectives.\n        Q0: np.array\n            Initial number of quarantineds.\n        contactMatrix: python function(t)\n             The social contact matrix C_{ij} denotes the\n             average number of contacts made per day by an\n             individual in class i with an individual in class j\n        testRate: python function(t)\n             Rate at which symptomatic and random individuals get tested\n        Tf: float\n            Final time of integrator\n        Nf: Int\n            Number of time points to evaluate.\n        Ti: float, optional\n            Start time of integrator.  2588:         Simulates a compartment model given initial conditions,

 2597:         x0: np.array or dict
 2598:             Initial conditions. If it is an array it should have length
 2599:             M*(model_dimension-1), where x0[i + j*M] should be the initial
 2600:             value of model class i of age group j. The removed R class
 2601:             must be left out. If it is a dict then
 2602:             it should have a key corresponding to each model class,
 2603:             with a 1D array containing the initial condition for each
 2604:             age group as value. One of the classes may be left out,
 2605:             in which case its initial values will be inferred from the
 2606:             others.
 2607:         contactMatrix: python function(t)
 2608:              The social contact matrix C_{ij} denotes the
 2609:              average number of contacts made per day by an
 2610:              individual in class i with an individual in class j
 2611:         Tf: float
 2612:             Final time of integrator
 2613:         Nf: Int

 2720:     """
 2721:     DEPRECATED.
 2722:     
 2723:     Susceptible, Exposed, Infected, Removed (SEI5R)
 2724:     The infected class has 5 groups:
 2725: 
 2726:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 2727:     * Is: symptomatic
 2728:     * Ih: hospitalized
 2729:     * Ic: ICU
 2730:     * Im: Mortality
 2731: 
 2732:     ...
 2733: 
 2734:     Parameters
 2735:     ----------
 2736:     parameters: dict
 2737:         Contains the following keys:
 2738: 
 2739:         alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 2740:             Fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 2741:         beta: float
 2742:             Rate of spread of infection.
 2743:         gE: float
 2744:             Rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 2745:         gIa: float
 2746:             Rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 2747:         gIs: float
 2748:             Rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 2749:         gIh: float
 2750:             Rate of removal for hospitalised individuals.
 2751:         gIc: float
 2752:             Rate of removal for idividuals in intensive care.
 2753:         fsa: float
 2754:             Fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 2755:         fh  : float
 2756:             Fraction by which hospitalised individuals are isolated.
 2757:         sa: float, np.array (M,)
 2758:             Daily arrival of new susceptables.
 2759:         hh: float, np.array (M,)
 2760:             Fraction hospitalised from Is
 2761:         cc: float, np.array (M,)
 2762:             Fraction sent to intensive care from hospitalised.
 2763:         mm: float, np.array (M,)
 2764:             mortality rate in intensive care
 2765:     M: int
 2766:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 2767:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 2768:     Ni: np.array(M, )
 2769:         Initial number in each compartment and class
